@NODE "Mail_4" " Re: Bitplane Addresses "
From: Curt Esser <camge@amigaonline.net>
Date: 07-30-00 12:20:38
Subject: @{b}Re: Bitplane Addresses@{ub}

Hi Tom,

> I need to find out the addresses of each bitplane in a bitmap. I presume I
can do this by
> looking at the newtype .BitMap with amigalibs.res resident, but I don't
know the name of the > offset for each bitplane. Could someone e-mail me (or
the list) this information.

Here is the OS BitMap structure:

BytesPerRow.w
Rows.w
Flags.b
Depth.b
pad.w
*Planes.l[8]

Keep in mind, this is the OS's structure, which is NOT the same as the Blitz
BitMap object.

So, to access it you would do this (assuming you are using Blitz Bitmap 0):

MyBMap.BitMap = Peek.l(Addr BitMap(0))

Now to get the address of the first two bitplanes, you could do this:

*firstplane = MyBMap\Planes[0]
*secondplane=MyBMap\Planes[1]


> Also I would > like to know the offsets for all the other intuition
objects, can anyone help?

Yes, just load amigalibs.res into the Blitz editor, and select "View
Newtypes" from the menu.

This will open a window with all the newtypes in it, and you can select the
one you want to see the info.

