Hi Daniel

>     In which way I can open a screen with more than 256 colours (HAM, HAM8) and
> create a bitmap with depth larger than 8??? Is that possible to do? 

I think there is a flag you can set for specifying a screen to be HAM or HAM8, 
and you'd need to use the long version of the Screen command:

Screen 0,0,0,320,200,6,$800,"test",0,1 ; HAM screen, 320x200
Screen 0,0,0,320,200,8,$8804,"test",0,1 ; HAM8 hires screen 320x200

However, if you wanted to open a screen width a depth of >8 then you could 
probably do it using the ScreenTags command, or the NScreen command. If not, 
then you'll definately be able to do it with OpenScreen_. You may need to 
specify the correct screenmode ID, which you can get with an ASL requester, or 
maybe with the BestModeIDA_ command (although that way isn't very good).

If you want to allocate a bitmap with depth larger than 8, you'd either have to 
