Well, it appears that there's only one thing that prevents me from making it
work. I've come up with the following code, which starts executing when my
window gets the IDCMP_INACTIVEWINDOW message:

InBack.b=True
While InBack

    lock.l = LockIBase_(0)
    *firstscreen._Screen = IntuitionBase\FirstScreen ; the problem spot
    UnlockIBase_(lock)

    If Peek.l(Addr Screen(0)) = *firstscreen
        InBack.b=False
    EndIf

    For i = 1 To 50
        WaitTOF_
    Next i

Wend

In the marked line Blitz reports garbage at the end of line. It appears that
it doesn't recognise IntuitionBase\FirstScreen. IntuitionBase tokenizes and
it obviously isn't understood as a NewType with FirstScreen field. I found
the struct in the autodocs and I'd be able to access it in C but my
knowledge of Blitz is obviously too limited.

At the same time I'd like to ask whether there is any better solution to the
periodic poleing with a WaitTOF_ loop? Interrupts obviously wouldn't work
(intuition calls) so I don't see any other solution.

