> A good idea, and should be fairly straightforward. Don't know if it'll work
> though, might screw with the stack a bit too much, but I'll give it a go unless
> someone else gets it working.

Hmm, maybe not such a good idea. Was just reading my 68k manual and when you 
get interrupts the return address of whatever was interrupted gets stuck on the 
stack (obviously). However, there would be a problem if you had interrupted an 
interrupt - since changing the return address would mean that some interrupt 
handler never gets completed.

And then there's the problem of your interrupt being called when its another 
task that was running (same problem as above, not returning to the right place).

And finally, I don't know how it works in Blitz, but there is a piece of OS 
code that gets called before all the interrupt service routines are called (by 
the OS code). So you couldn't really return back skipping that OS code.

I don't think that'll work.

