Not a bug, just implemented a bit lamely - they should have checked for the 
presence of the CustomScreen tag, but they've obviosuly stuck in their own one 
with the currently used Screen.

So, if the window is one you have opened with the Blitz Screen (or ScreenTags) 
command, simply do a "Use Screen x" before WindowTags.

If you have opened the window using OS commands, or it is a public screen you 
are trying to open on, you'll need to do a "FindScreen x,title$" to grab it as 
a Blitz screen and then "Use Screen x"

