Hi Tony,


Few thing you might be intersted to know:
The UAE emulation is quite fast here on a PII 350, but disk access remains very
slow.

I had both linux and dos versions installed.

Disk access is faster on the linux version than the dos version. (On the dos
version UAE maintain special files to manage the dos file names being 8.3
letters wide. Those files stand in each directory and include the full and
mangled files names.)

However the emulation itself is slower on that very same linux version.
Note another advantage of linux with UAE is that you can mount ffs partitions
rw in linux, so you could for example unplug your hd from the miga and use that
directly with UAE.

You can use blitz but won't be able to do time-critical tasks because the clock
goes crazy and un-regular.

It's like if you were having a flickerfixer+scandoubler and this is a *great*
advantage compared to the original 1200 from my pow (seen the price of those
